crease the reader’s delight in his learned but witty, scalding but poetic, satire.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 27. Okt 2021) 0aSpanish fiction. 7aLITERARY CRITICISM / General.2bisacsh1 aFearing, Kelly.1 aSchade, George D.40uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9780292753228423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9780292753228/original  aEBA_BACKALL  aEBA_CL_LT  aEBA_EBACKALL  aEBA_EBKALL  aEBA_ECL_LT  aEBA_EEBKALL  aEBA_ESSHALL  aEBA_PPALL  aEBA_SSHALL  aGBV-deGruyter-alles  aPDA11SSHE  aPDA13ENGE  aPDA17SSHEE  aPDA5EBK